        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27296",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I mean the setWeekDay follows the ISO standard, so sunday is '7'.\nBut if use toArray() of Zend_Date, the weekday will be '0' as the GNU standard.\n\nI suggest that use one rule for Zend_Date, not two different kind of rule.\nIt will make people confused.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-14T23:48:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-14T23:48:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27298",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Why would this be a problem when both rules are supported ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-15T00:41:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-15T00:41:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27299",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It is not consistent.\n\nPlease consider below situation:\n\n$a->setWeekDay(7);\n\n$b = $a->toArray();\n$weekDay = $b['weekday'];\n\necho $weekDay (It is 0, not 7)\n\n------------------------------------------------\nBut if it is consistent.\nThen we can define a constant to check it.\n\ndefine('SUNDAY', 0);  ( Or 7 if ISO standard)\n\n$a->setWeekDay(SUNDAY);\n$b = $a->toArray();\n$weekDay = $b['weekday'];\n\necho $weekDay==SUNDAY (This will be true, because it is consistent)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=liber",
                        "name": "liber",
                        "displayName": "Liber Chen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-15T00:58:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-15T00:58:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27300",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
